hine — runtime memory areas, garbage collection algorithms and collectors, class loading, and monitoring tools.","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/java/java-jvm.md","sourceDirName":"technical-knowledge/java","slug":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-jvm","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-jvm","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"tags":[],"version":"current","frontMatter":{"id":"java-jvm","title":"JVM Internals: Memory, GC & Class Loading","slug":"java-jvm"},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Java I/O: Streams, NIO & I/O Models","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-io"},"next":{"title":"Java New Features: Java 8 through Java 21+","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-new-features"}},{"id":"technical-knowledge/java/java-new-features","title":"Java New Features: Java 8 through Java 21+","description":"A practical guide to the most impactful features introduced in modern Java versions — from lambdas and streams (Java 8) to virtual threads and pattern matching (Java 21).","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/java/java-new-features.md","sourceDirName":"technical-knowledge/java","slug":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-new-features","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-new-features","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"tags":[],"version":"current","frontMatter":{"id":"java-new-features","title":"Java New Features: Java 8 through Java 21+","slug":"java-new-features"},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"JVM Internals: Memory, GC & Class Loading","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-jvm"},"next":{"title":"Java Interview Questions & Answers","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-interview-questions"}},{"id":"technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-complete-guide","title":"Kafka: The Complete Guide","description":"Apache Kafka is a distributed event-streaming platform designed for high-throughput, fault-tolerant, real-time data pipelines and streaming applications. This guide covers the core concepts every new learner needs to understand.","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/kafka/Kafka: The Complete Guide.md","sourceDirName":"technical-knowledge/kafka","slug":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-complete-guide","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-complete-guide","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"tags":[],"version":"current","frontMatter":{"id":"kafka-complete-guide","title":"Kafka: The Complete Guide","slug":"kafka-complete-guide"},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Java Interview Questions & Answers","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/java/java-interview-questions"},"next":{"title":"Kafka Connect","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-connect"}},{"id":"technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-connect","title":"Kafka Connect","description":"Kafka Connect is a framework for streaming data between Apache Kafka and external systems (databases, key-value stores, search indexes, file systems, etc.) using reusable connectors.","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-connect.md","sourceDirName":"technical-knowledge/kafka","slug":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-connect","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-connect","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"tags":[],"version":"current","frontMatter":{"id":"kafka-connect","title":"Kafka Connect","slug":"kafka-connect"},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Kafka: The Complete Guide","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-complete-guide"},"next":{"title":"Kafka Streams: Topology & Branching","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-streams"}},{"id":"technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-exactly-once","title":"Configuring Exactly-Once Semantics in Kafka","description":"Exactly-once semantics (EOS) ensures that every message is delivered and processed exactly once — no duplicates, no data loss. This guide covers how to configure EOS across producers, consumers, Kafka Streams, and Kafka Connect.","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-exactly-once.md","sourceDirName":"technical-knowledge/kafka","slug":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-exactly-once","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-exactly-once","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"tags":[],"version":"current","frontMatter":{"id":"kafka-exactly-once","title":"Configuring Exactly-Once Semantics in Kafka","slug":"kafka-exactly-once"},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Kafka Streams: Topology & Branching","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-streams"},"next":{"title":"Parallel Consumer in Kafka","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-parallel-consumer"}},{"id":"technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-parallel-consumer","title":"Parallel Consumer in Kafka","description":"Standard Kafka consumers process messages sequentially per partition — one message at a time per assigned partition. This becomes a bottleneck when downstream processing is slow (e.g., HTTP calls, database writes). Parallel consumers break this limit by processing multiple messages concurrently within a single partition.","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-parallel-consumer.md","sourceDirName":"technical-knowledge/kafka","slug":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-parallel-consumer","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-parallel-consumer","draft":false,"unlisted":false,"tags":[],"version":"current","frontMatter":{"id":"kafka-parallel-consumer","title":"Parallel Consumer in Kafka","slug":"kafka-parallel-consumer"},"sidebar":"tutorialSidebar","previous":{"title":"Configuring Exactly-Once Semantics in Kafka","permalink":"/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-exactly-once"}},{"id":"technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-streams","title":"Kafka Streams: Topology & Branching","description":"Kafka Streams is a lightweight client library for building real-time stream-processing applications on top of Apache Kafka. This guide covers its programming model, the topology concept, and branching patterns.","source":"@site/docs/technical-knowledge/kafka/kafka-streams.md","sourceDirName":"technical-know